NOw I need to push some files and some want to skip how do I do in intellij

Got it — you want to push only some files and skip others in IntelliJ IDEA 👍
There are a few clean ways to do this depending on what you want.

✅ ✅ Method 1: Use IntelliJ Commit Window (Best way)
Steps:
Open Commit panel
Shortcut: Ctrl + K (Windows)
You’ll see a list of changed files
✔ Select ONLY the files you want to push
❌ Uncheck the files you want to skip
Click:
Commit (or)
Commit and Push

👉 Only selected files will go to Git

✅ Method 2: Add specific files manually (Git way)

In terminal inside IntelliJ:

git add file1.java
git add file2.java

Then:

git commit -m "Added selected files"
git push

👉 Files you didn’t add will be ignored

✅ Method 3: Permanently ignore files (.gitignore)

If there are files you never want to push (like logs, build files):

Create or edit .gitignore
Add entries like:
node_modules/
*.log
target/
.idea/

👉 IntelliJ will automatically stop tracking them

⚠️ Important cases
🔴 File already committed once?

Even if you ignore it now, Git still tracks it.

Fix:

git rm --cached filename

Then commit again.

💡 Pro Tip (IntelliJ feature)

Right-click file →
👉 Git → Add to .gitignore

Super easy 👍

